In [4]:
def neural_network_model(inp, seed):    
    np.random.seed(seed)    
    
    initializer = tf.initializers.random_normal
    activation_hl1 = tf.nn.sigmoid
    activation_out = None
    num_output_nodes = 1
    
    tf.logging.set_verbosity(tf.logging.ERROR)
    hidden_layer_1 = tf.layers.dense(inputs=inp,
                                    units=K,
                                    activation=activation_hl1,
                                    kernel_initializer=initializer())
    output_layer = tf.layers.dense(inputs=hidden_layer_1,
                                  units=num_output_nodes,
                                  activation=activation_out,
                                  use_bias=False,
                                  kernel_initializer=initializer())
    return output_layer
In [5]:
def train_neural_net(sess, seed):    
    alpha = neural_network_model(inp, seed)
    cost = tf.reduce_mean(tf.square(alpha - target_fcn))
    optimizer = tf.train.GradientDescentOptimizer(dt)
    
    train = optimizer.minimize(cost)
    gErr = []
    trErr = []
    
    sess.run(tf.global_variables_initializer())
    
    for m in range(0,M):        
        n = np.random.randint(0, N)
        x_in = x_training[n:n+1]
        sess.run(train, feed_dict={inp:x_in})
        
        if m % int(M/100) == 0:
            gErr.append(cost.eval(feed_dict={inp:x_test}))
            trErr.append(cost.eval(feed_dict={inp:x_training}))
        if m % int(M/10) == 0:
            print(m)
    
    return alpha, gErr, trErr

%%capture --no-display
start = time.time()
for K in Ks:
    x_training_N = {N:None for N in Ns}
    training_data_vals = {N:None for N in Ns} 
    alpha_vals_N = {N:None for N in Ns}
    gErr_N = {N:None for N in Ns}
    trErr_N = {N:None for N in Ns}
    
    for N in Ns:
        np.random.seed(seed)
        x_training = np.random.uniform(-4, 4, size=(N,1))
        x_test = np.random.uniform(-4, 4, size=(N,1))
        with tf.Session() as sess:
            training_data_vals[N] = target_fcn.eval(feed_dict={inp:x_training})
            x_training_N[N] = x_training
    
        alpha_vals = {dt:None for dt in dts}
        gErr = {dt:None for dt in dts}
        trErr = {dt:None for dt in dts}
    
        for dt in dts:
            with tf.Session() as sess:
                alpha, gErr[dt], trErr[dt] = train_neural_net(sess, seed)
                #target_fcn_vals = target_fcn.eval(feed_dict={inp:pts})
                alpha_vals[dt] = alpha.eval(feed_dict={inp:pts})
            
        alpha_vals_N[N] = alpha_vals
        gErr_N[N] = gErr
        trErr_N[N] = trErr
    
    all_train_data_vals[K] = training_data_vals
    all_x_training[K] = x_training_N
    all_alpha_vals[K] = alpha_vals_N
    all_gErr[K] = gErr_N
    all_trErr[K] = trErr_N
    
end = time.time()

%%capture --no-display
start = time.time()
for K in Ks:
    x_training_N = {N:None for N in Ns}
    training_data_vals = {N:None for N in Ns} 
    alpha_vals_N = {N:None for N in Ns}
    gErr_N = {N:None for N in Ns}
    trErr_N = {N:None for N in Ns}
    
    for N in Ns:
        np.random.seed(seed)
        x_training = np.random.uniform(-4, 4, size=(N,1))
        x_test = np.random.uniform(-4, 4, size=(N,1))
        with tf.Session() as sess:
            training_data_vals[N] = target_fcn.eval(feed_dict={inp:x_training})
            x_training_N[N] = x_training
    
        alpha_vals = {dt:None for dt in dts}
        gErr = {dt:None for dt in dts}
        trErr = {dt:None for dt in dts}
    
        for dt in dts:
            with tf.Session() as sess:
                alpha, gErr[dt], trErr[dt] = train_neural_net(sess, seed)
                #target_fcn_vals = target_fcn.eval(feed_dict={inp:pts})
                alpha_vals[dt] = alpha.eval(feed_dict={inp:pts})
            
        alpha_vals_N[N] = alpha_vals
        gErr_N[N] = gErr
        trErr_N[N] = trErr
    
    all_train_data_vals[K] = training_data_vals
    all_x_training[K] = x_training_N
    all_alpha_vals[K] = alpha_vals_N
    all_gErr[K] = gErr_N
    all_trErr[K] = trErr_N
    
end = time.time()

 def neural_network_model2a(inp, seed):    
    np.random.seed(seed)    
    
    initializer = tf.initializers.random_normal
    bias_init_unif = tf.initializers.random_uniform
    activation_hl1 = tf.nn.sigmoid
    activation_out = None
    num_output_nodes = 1
    
    tf.logging.set_verbosity(tf.logging.ERROR)
    hidden_layer_1 = tf.layers.dense(inputs=inp,
                                    units=K,
                                    activation=activation_hl1,
                                    use_bias=True,
                                    bias_initializer=bias_init_unif(minval=20*np.pi, maxval=22*np.pi), 
                                    kernel_initializer=initializer())
    output_layer = tf.layers.dense(inputs=hidden_layer_1,
                                  units=num_output_nodes,
                                  activation=activation_out,
                                  use_bias=False,
                                  kernel_initializer=initializer())
    return output_layer

    activation_hl1 = tf.math.sin
    activation_out = None
    num_output_nodes = 1
    
    tf.logging.set_verbosity(tf.logging.ERROR)
    hidden_layer_1 = tf.layers.dense(inputs=inp,
                                    units=K,
                                    activation=activation_hl1,
                                    use_bias=True,
                                    bias_initializer=bias_init_unif(minval=20*np.pi, maxval=22*np.pi), 
                                    kernel_initializer=initializer())
    output_layer = tf.layers.dense(inputs=hidden_layer_1,
                                  units=num_output_nodes,
                                  activation=activation_out,
                                  use_bias=False,
                                  kernel_initializer=initializer())
    return output_layer
In [224]:
def train_neural_net2(sess, seed):    
    alpha1 = neural_network_model2a(inp, seed)
    alpha2 = neural_network_model2b(inp, seed)
    cost1 = tf.reduce_mean(tf.square(alpha1 - target_fcn))
    cost2 = tf.reduce_mean(tf.square(alpha2 - target_fcn))
    optimizer = tf.train.GradientDescentOptimizer(dt)
    
    train1 = optimizer.minimize(cost1)
    train2 = optimizer.minimize(cost2)
    gErr1 = []; gErr2 = []
    trErr1 = []; trErr2 = []
    
    sess.run(tf.global_variables_initializer())
    
    for m in range(0,M):        
        n = np.random.randint(0, N)
        x_in = x_training[n:n+1]
        sess.run(train1, feed_dict={inp:x_in})
        
        if m % int(M/100) == 0:
            gErr1.append(cost1.eval(feed_dict={inp:x_test}))
            trErr1.append(cost1.eval(feed_dict={inp:x_training}))
        if m % int(M/10) == 0:
            print(m)
            
        sess.run(train2, feed_dict={inp:x_in})
        
        if m % int(M/100) == 0:
            gErr2.append(cost2.eval(feed_dict={inp:x_test}))
            trErr2.append(cost2.eval(feed_dict={inp:x_training}))
        if m % int(M/10) == 0:
            print(m)
    
    return alpha1, alpha2, gErr1, trErr1, gErr2, trErr2

%%capture --no-display
start = time.time()
for K in Ks:
    #x_training_nn = {nn:None for nn in [1,2]}
    #training_data_vals = {nn:None for nn in [1,2]} 
    alpha_vals_nn = {nn:None for nn in [1,2]}
    gErr_nn = {nn:None for nn in [1,2]}
    trErr_nn = {nn:None for nn in [1,2]}
    
    #for nn in [1,2]:
    np.random.seed(seed)
    x_training = np.random.uniform(-4, 4, size=(Ns[0],1))
    x_test = np.random.uniform(-4, 4, size=(Ns[0],1))
    with tf.Session() as sess:
        training_data_vals = target_fcn.eval(feed_dict={inp:x_training})
        #x_training_nn[nn] = x_training
    
    alpha_vals1 = {dt:None for dt in dts}
    gErr1 = {dt:None for dt in dts}
    trErr1 = {dt:None for dt in dts}
    alpha_vals2 = {dt:None for dt in dts}
    gErr2 = {dt:None for dt in dts}
    trErr2 = {dt:None for dt in dts}
    
    for dt in dts:
        with tf.Session() as sess:
            alpha1, alpha2, gErr1[dt], trErr1[dt], gErr2[dt], trErr2[dt] = train_neural_net2(sess, seed)
            #target_fcn_vals = target_fcn.eval(feed_dict={inp:pts})
            alpha_vals1[dt] = alpha1.eval(feed_dict={inp:pts})
            alpha_vals2[dt] = alpha2.eval(feed_dict={inp:pts})
            
    alpha_vals_nn[1] = alpha_vals1
    alpha_vals_nn[2] = alpha_vals2
    gErr_nn[1] = gErr1
    gErr_nn[2] = gErr2
    trErr_nn[1] = trErr1
    trErr_nn[2] = trErr2
    
    all_train_data_vals[K] = training_data_vals
    all_x_training[K] = x_training
    all_alpha_vals[K] = alpha_vals_nn
    all_gErr[K] = gErr_nn
    all_trErr[K] = trErr_nn
    
end = time.time()

In [ ]:
# Just use logic: for each additional dimension, for each point in the sample of N from the original dimension,
# we need to take another N data points from the new dimension in order to maintain roughly the same sampling
# density; thus, if for #dim = 1 we need 100 data points to obtain a certain sampling density, then for 
# #dim = 2 we need to sample 100 data points from the new dimension for each of the 100 data points from the 
# old one, giving us a sample of 100^2 for #dim = 2.
# In general for #dim = d, we need N^d data points in order to maintain the same sampling density as with N 
# data points in #dim = 1. In other words, the sample size required will grow polynomially with the number
# of dimension of the data space. This is the so-called "curse of dimensionality"
